---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'healthcare-system', text: 'Healthcare System', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-requirements', text: 'Visa Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'insurance-requirements', text: 'Insurance Requirements', level: 2 },
  { id: 'recommended-providers', text: 'Recommended Providers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'costs', text: 'Expected Costs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'scenarios', text: 'Real-World Scenarios', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Poland Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/poland/insurance' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors' },
  { title: 'Czech Republic for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/czech-republic' },
  { title: 'Germany for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/germany' },
  { title: 'Hungary for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/hungary' },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'entryAge', header: 'Max Entry Age' },
  { key: 'renewal', header: 'Renewal' },
  { key: 'monthlyFrom', header: 'From (65-69)' },
  { key: 'polandFit', header: 'Poland Fit' },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'PLN 1,400-2,000/mo', polandFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'BUPA Global', entryAge: '79', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'PLN 1,650-2,300/mo', polandFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'PLN 1,300-1,850/mo', polandFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'AXA Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'PLN 1,200-1,700/mo', polandFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Polish NFZ (Public)', entryAge: 'No limit', renewal: 'N/A', monthlyFrom: '9% income', polandFit: 'For Residents' },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'International Insurance (65-69)', monthly: 'PLN 1,300-2,000', annual: 'PLN 15,600-24,000' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (70-74)', monthly: 'PLN 1,800-2,600', annual: 'PLN 21,600-31,200' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (75-79)', monthly: 'PLN 2,400-3,500', annual: 'PLN 28,800-42,000' },
  { category: 'Polish NFZ (Public)', monthly: '9% of income', annual: 'Contribution-based' },
  { category: 'Polish Private (Medicover)', monthly: 'PLN 200-600', annual: 'PLN 2,400-7,200' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in Poland 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors retiring in Poland. NFZ public healthcare, Warsaw and Krakow hospitals, visa options, and coverage for expats 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in Poland"
  subheadline="Poland offers affordable European living, improving healthcare, rich history, and EU membership—with straightforward residence options for retirees."
  heroImage="/images/countries/poland-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose Poland</h2>
  <p>
    Poland has emerged as an attractive retirement destination offering low cost of living, EU membership, improving infrastructure, and a fascinating blend of history and modernity. Major cities offer good healthcare at fraction of Western European costs.
  </p>

  <p>
    Krakow is the cultural heart with historic charm and good hospitals. Warsaw provides capital-city amenities and best healthcare options. Wrocław and Gdańsk offer alternatives with strong quality of life. Smaller cities provide even greater value.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> Improving; private sector excellent in cities</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> Polish; English growing, especially younger generation</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> PLN 5,000-9,000/month (~€1,100-2,000)</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Continental; cold winters, warm summers</li>
      <li><strong>EU Status:</strong> Full EU member (not Eurozone; uses PLN)</li>
      <li><strong>Value:</strong> Among EU's most affordable countries</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">Poland's Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    Poland has public healthcare (NFZ - Narodowy Fundusz Zdrowia) funded through mandatory contributions. Quality varies—public hospitals can be crowded with long waits. Private healthcare has grown rapidly and offers excellent care in major cities.
  </p>

  <p>
    Private clinics like Medicover, LUX MED, and Enel-Med provide modern facilities, English-speaking staff, and short wait times. Costs are fraction of Western Europe. Many expats use private care as primary, keeping NFZ as backup.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Public vs Private Reality</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      Polish public healthcare (NFZ) has long wait times—months for specialist appointments, sometimes years for elective surgery. Private healthcare is affordable (PLN 200-600/month for comprehensive plans) and provides faster, better service. Most expats rely primarily on private care.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    Poland offers straightforward residence options:
  </p>

  <h3>Temporary Residence Permit</h3>
  <p>
    For those demonstrating sufficient financial means (typically PLN 3,000+/month) and health insurance. Valid 3 years, renewable. Can lead to permanent residence after 5 years.
  </p>

  <h3>Poland's D Visa (Long-Stay)</h3>
  <p>
    Initial entry for those planning to apply for residence. Valid up to 1 year. Requires health insurance and proof of financial means.
  </p>

  <h3>EU Citizens</h3>
  <p>
    Free movement applies. Register after 90 days with proof of income and health insurance. Can access NFZ system once contributing.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance requirements for Poland:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Residence application:</strong> Comprehensive health insurance required</li>
    <li><strong>EU citizens:</strong> EHIC initially; can join NFZ</li>
    <li><strong>After residence:</strong> Can voluntarily join NFZ or use private</li>
    <li><strong>Private recommended:</strong> Most expats prefer private care quality</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for Poland</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      International insurance works well for Poland—it's accepted for residence applications. Many add Polish private insurance (Medicover, LUX MED) for excellent local care at low cost. Keep international for travel and potential evacuation to more advanced facilities if needed.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors in Poland, these providers offer strong coverage at good value:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for Poland</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Good European network, accepted for residence</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Highest entry age (79), comprehensive coverage</li>
    <li><strong>Allianz Care:</strong> Competitive pricing for Central Europe</li>
    <li><strong>Polish Private:</strong> Medicover, LUX MED offer excellent local care cheaply</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare coverage and pricing from providers that accept seniors for Poland.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs for Poland are among the EU's lowest:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Polish private:</strong> PLN 300-500/month for excellent Medicover coverage</li>
    <li><strong>Combined approach:</strong> International for visa + Polish private for daily care</li>
    <li><strong>Higher deductibles:</strong> PLN 10,000+ deductible reduces international premiums</li>
    <li><strong>Direct pay:</strong> Polish private care is so cheap, paying cash is viable</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: American Retiree, 68</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $2,200/month pension. Moving to Krakow for affordable living and culture.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Cigna Global for residence. Add Medicover VIP for local care. Cigna for US visits.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> Cigna ~PLN 1,600/month + Medicover ~PLN 400/month. Total ~$500/month comprehensive.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: British Couple, Both 71</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> Post-Brexit, retiring to Warsaw. £2,500/month combined pension.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> BUPA Global for both. Add LUX MED Polish private. Excellent combined coverage.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> BUPA ~PLN 4,000/month combined + LUX MED ~PLN 600/month. Comprehensive at great value.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: German EU Citizen, 66</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> EU citizen retiring from Berlin to Wrocław. German pension €1,600/month.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> EHIC initially. Register for NFZ if contributing. Add Medicover for quality care.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> NFZ/EHIC + Medicover ~PLN 350/month + Allianz ~PLN 1,200/month for Germany.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Poland really that affordable?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Yes. Among EU's cheapest. A comfortable retirement in Krakow or Warsaw costs PLN 7,000-10,000/month (~€1,500-2,200). Smaller cities are even cheaper. Healthcare, restaurants, utilities, and services are fraction of Western Europe. Quality of life is high.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Why do expats prefer Polish private healthcare?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Polish public healthcare (NFZ) has long wait times and crowded facilities. Private providers (Medicover, LUX MED) offer modern clinics, short waits, English-speaking staff, and comprehensive care for PLN 300-600/month. It's excellent value.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Do I need to speak Polish?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        In major cities, English is increasingly common, especially among younger Poles and in private healthcare. Administrative processes are in Polish. Outside major cities, English is limited. Learning basic Polish improves daily life significantly.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How cold are Polish winters?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Cold. Warsaw averages -3 to 2°C in January; Krakow similar. Snow is common. Buildings are well-heated. If you dislike cold, Poland's continental climate with distinct seasons may be challenging. Summers are pleasant (20-25°C).
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes from providers that specialize in senior expat coverage for Poland.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Insurance requirements, visa regulations, and healthcare access rules change regularly. Always verify current requirements with Polish authorities and consult with a licensed insurance professional.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
